      "label": "Condition",
      "value": "The top, bottom and right sides of the papyrus are broken off. There are two large lacunae in the left half of the papyrus. The text on the verso has been written before the recto. The top and the bottom of the text are incomplete. The incision on the left side, which forms a straight margin on the recto, cuts through the text on the left side of the recto."
