      "label": "Further remarks",
      "value": ""
    },
    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Recto: The sender uses a plural for the addressees and warns the addressee to execute something precisely (l. 7).\n\u00a0\nVerso: The sender informs the addressee that he writes him immediately to prevent the addressee from hasting to send him another letter or to blame him for delaying his response (ll. 2-3). He also requests the addressee to buy him something perhaps beans and lentils (ll. 3-4). Finally the sender writes that he has sent a certain Ab\u016b Qays something (l. 4)."
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "There are diacritical dots in two places and sin has an oblique stroke over it"
    }
  ],
